<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7384&amp;p=72744#p72744"><![CDATA[
Games do it by writing to the nametable area of PPU memory during VBlank.  :-)  Remember, VBlank happens 60 times a second (or 50 for PAL systems).<br /><br />You *can* write to NTs during VBlank, but it's tricky in the sense that adjusting some of the $2005/2006 registers causes the PPU to do things that you might not expect it to.  Since you're starting out, stick to writing to the PPU during VBlank and you should be fine.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Sat Jan 15, 2011 4:00 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
